rst class of female astronomers: <em>=E2=80=9CNo woman should say=2C =E2=
=80=98I am but a woman!=E2=80=99 But a woman! What more can you ask to be?=
=E2=80=9D</em> Although Meitner showed a gift for mathematics from an earl=
y age=2C there was little correlation between aptitude and opportunity for=
 women in 19th-century Europe. At the end of her long life=2C she would re=
count=2C not bitterly but wistfully:</p><blockquote style=3D"-webkit-text-=
